  "text": "2.3. The Caffarelli-Silvestre extension problem. It has been shown in [CITATION_1] that any power of the fractional Laplacian in R n can be determined as an operator that maps a Dirichlet boundary condition to a Neumann-type condition via an extension problem posed on R n+1 + . For a bounded domain, an analogous result has been obtained in [CITATION_2] for s = 1 2 , and in [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] for any s ∈ (0, 1). Let us briefly describe these results. Consider a function u defined on Ω. We define the α-harmonic extension of u to the cylinder C, as the function u that solves the boundary value problem ",
